        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): archive short-term promotions outside MEMORY.md",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR changes short-term memory promotion to archive detailed promoted excerpts instead of appending them directly to root `MEMORY.md`.\n\nDetailed promotion dumps now go to:\n\n```text\nmemory/archived/YYYY-Q#/memory-promoted-short-term-dump-YYYY-MM-DD.md\n```\n\n`MEMORY.md` keeps a compact `Promoted From Short-Term Memory` pointer section with the latest archive path. Existing detailed root promotion sections are migrated into the archive pointer flow the next time promotion apply runs.\n\nThe patch also updates CLI help, managed Dreaming report wording, and promotion events. Promotion events now include optional `archivePath` and `archiveRelativePath` fields for archive-aware consumers while remaining compatible with historical event records.\n\n## Why\n\nRoot `MEMORY.md` is intended to stay compact and index-like. Appending full promoted excerpts into it can cause repeated size-alert / cleanup cycles. Archive-first promotion preserves the durable details while keeping root context small.\n\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- **Behavior or issue addressed**: Short-term promotion should archive detailed promoted excerpts under `memory/archived/YYYY-Q#/memory-promoted-short-term-dump-YYYY-MM-DD.md` while keeping root `MEMORY.md` compact with a latest-archive pointer, and repeated apply runs should reconcile archived markers without duplicating promotion detail. The follow-up docs/help change documents the archive path and workspace `.gitignore` choices for users who version-control their workspace.\n- **Real environment tested**: Disposable OpenClaw workspace using this PR's source implementation on Linux with Node 22. No live install, Gateway, cron job, production config, or user workspace state was modified.\n- **Exact steps or command run after this patch**: Created a disposable workspace with root `MEMORY.md` plus one daily memory note; recorded one short-term recall; ranked promotion candidates; ran promotion apply; inspected root `MEMORY.md` and the archive dump; then simulated stale promotion metadata and ran apply again to verify archive-aware reconciliation. After the docs/help follow-up and rebase cleanup at head `51a65360bf85`, also ran `git diff --check`, conflict-marker scan, merge-tree against `upstream/main`, `corepack pnpm exec oxfmt --check CHANGELOG.md docs/cli/memory.md extensions/memory-core/src/cli.ts extensions/memory-core/src/cli.test.ts`, `corepack pnpm exec oxlint CHANGELOG.md docs/cli/memory.md extensions/memory-core/src/cli.ts extensions/memory-core/src/cli.test.ts`, targeted extension-memory Vitest, and `node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo`.\n- **Evidence after fix**: Copied terminal output from the isolated archive-first proof run:\n\n  ```text\n  Archive-first short-term promotion proof\n  workspace: $WORKSPACE (disposable)\n  candidate_count=1\n  before_memory_bytes=58\n  first_apply applied=1 appended=1 reconciledExisting=0\n  archive_relative=memory/archived/2026-Q2/memory-promoted-short-term-dump-2026-05-07.md\n  after_memory_bytes=439\n  memory_has_pointer=true\n  memory_has_promotion_marker=false\n  memory_has_detailed_excerpt=false\n  memory_preserved_existing_section=true\n  archive_has_marker=true\n  archive_has_detailed_excerpt=true\n  second_apply applied=1 appended=0 reconciledExisting=1\n  archive_marker_count_after_second=1\n  memory_path=$WORKSPACE/MEMORY.md\n  archive_path=$WORKSPACE/memory/archived/2026-Q2/memory-promoted-short-term-dump-2026-05-07.md\n  ```\n\n  Docs/help validation before rebase passed:\n\n  ```text\n  oxfmt: All matched files use the correct format.\n  oxlint: Found 0 warnings and 0 errors.\n  extension-memory targeted Vitest: Test Files 3 passed (3); Tests 100 passed (100)\n  tsgo extensions test config: exit 0\n  ```\n\n  Post-rebase structural checks passed:\n\n  ```text\n  git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD: pass\n  conflict-marker scan: no conflict markers\n  merge-tree against upstream/main: clean\n  ```\n\n- **Observed result after fix**: First apply wrote the detailed excerpt to `memory/archived/2026-Q2/memory-promoted-short-term-dump-2026-05-07.md`, left root `MEMORY.md` with a compact pointer and no promotion marker/detail, preserved the existing root section, and a second apply reconciled the archived marker without appending a duplicate. The current docs/help follow-up keeps the CLI subcommand help, docs, changelog, and test coverage aligned with that archive-first behavior.\n- **What was not tested**: Crash recovery between the archive write and root pointer write; very large long-term archive performance; full production Gateway activation; and mutating a real user workspace `.gitignore`. Those are intentionally outside this PR's isolated proof.\n\n## Tests\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.extension-memory.config.ts extensions/memory-core/src/short-term-promotion.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/cli.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory-events.test.ts\n```\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\n```\n\n```bash\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n## Notes\n\nThe archive + root pointer update is still a two-file write. A future follow-up could use temp-file + rename for stronger crash safety.\n\nArchive marker reconciliation currently scans existing quarterly dump files. If archive volume grows enough to make that expensive, a marker manifest/index would be a good follow-up.\n",
